Multiplayer philosophy:

server.c main runs at a port at a fixed hz rate, with ticks
server accepts connection

client sends Userjoin
server accepts Userjoin (username)

server replies with UserjoinACK

client recieves userjoinACK (contains map and player list)
client inmediatedly listens for ServerUpdate

*a

server sends ServerUpdate (contains entities (also players))

client reads ServerUpdate // Client has to remove himself from the client list from server update to avoid duplication
client applies ServerUpdate to his local world

client sends UserCmd (position and velocity)
server recieves UserCmd 
server decides its not ridiculous -> applies

goto *a
